From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Entrpi <entrpi@proton.me>
Date: Sat, 28 Feb 2026 13:46:33 +1100
Subject: [PATCH] drm/trilin-dptx: retry AUX on cold-plug timeout

When a display is connected after boot (cold-plug), the sink may not
be ready for AUX transactions immediately.  The DP spec allows up to
500ms for sink power-up, and some bridges need longer.

The driver was attempting a single DPCD read with no retry, causing
-ETIMEDOUT on first connect while subsequent unplug/replug cycles
worked fine (the sink was already powered).

Add a retry loop (5 attempts, 100ms apart) in handle_connect() when
read_sink_caps() returns -ETIMEDOUT, giving the sink up to 500ms
to become responsive.

Reported-by: coffnix (GitHub issue #10)
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/cix/dptx/trilin_dptx.c | 15 +++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 15 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/cix/dptx/trilin_dptx.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/cix/dptx/trilin_dptx.c
index 20a26ec845a17..c00ebf20ffe57 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/cix/dptx/trilin_dptx.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/cix/dptx/trilin_dptx.c
@@ -2590,6 +2590,21 @@ int trilin_dp_handle_connect(struct trilin_dp *dp, bool send_notification)
 	dp->state |= DP_STATE_CONNECTED;
 
 	rc = trinlin_dp_panel_read_sink_caps(dp);
+	/*
+	 * On cold-plug (display connected after boot), the sink may not be
+	 * ready for AUX transactions immediately.  The DP spec allows up to
+	 * 500ms for a sink to power up, but some bridges/monitors need more.
+	 * Retry with increasing delays before giving up.
+	 */
+	if (rc == -ETIMEDOUT) {
+		int retries;
+
+		for (retries = 0; retries < 5 && rc == -ETIMEDOUT; retries++) {
+			DP_INFO("sink not ready, retry %d/5\n", retries + 1);
+			msleep(100);
+			rc = trinlin_dp_panel_read_sink_caps(dp);
+		}
+	}
 	/*
 	 * ETIMEDOUT --> cable may have been removed
 	 * ENOTCONN --> no downstream device connected
